content: Tremendous support, great APP

We're very sorry you are frustrated with the interface. Any suggestions on how we can improve? We are working on version 6 right now. 

As for integrating QR Code, Scan to Spreadsheet can parse a QR Code on a comma character into different fields. We also have a barcode generator with Google Sheet instructions on our web site berrywing.com/barcode

content: This app used to be amazing. I've used it yearly for the past number of years when we got in new PCs to record serial numbers. This year however I'll have to find something else to use. They changed the interface to something that isn't near as functional as before, yes it's prettier, but not anywhere near as functional. Also whenever I have bulk scan on it alternates orientation between each scan and for whatever reason portrait mode isn't anywhere near as accurate as landscape so I had to turn bulk mode off and scan individually. Also for whatever reason it only registered 12 of my 25 scans, so now I'm sitting here and going to have to redo my work!
replyContent:
Hello Jason, 
We are mortified that you are disappointed in the app and that there are missing scans! Certainly not what we want to hear and we want to remedy this with you right away.

We want your detailed feedback on the interface changes that you are not happy with.
Please email us at softwaresupport@berrywing.com

content: I downloaded this app to use in my classroom this fall. replyContent:
Sorry to hear you are having a problem. We have a great barcode generator on our website. Also instructions on how to make many of them with Google Sheets. https://berrywing.com/barcode/

Email us at softwaresupport@berrywing.com

content: Had to update my review. The developer did some amazing work and really got this App up and running smooth. Great work and keep it up
replyContent: It is close to a year ago, and we have made many changes to the app since your review. I hope you like the new version. It matches the very popular Apple iOS version of the app with all the same features; like look up on scan and sharing the spreadsheets to other apps.

content: I have been using this apps for a couple years.  It was a little tricky to figure out at first but once you do it is seriously one of the best apps I have ever purchased.  This has saved me so much time and increased my inventory accuracy immensely! Highly recommend for anyone that need to scan items into a workable spreadsheet.  A+
replyContent: Thank you Cara! We appreciate you recommending the app. Knowing that it saved you time is very important to us.

Definitely wished I played with the app before really needing it. The scanner does not recognize barcodes quickly but once you get in a groove it becomes easier. Everything worked fine until upload. Originally I really liked this app but I think it works better on IOS than droid.  The IOS version has some better features like setting up a default template which I don't see at all in the Android version.  So you can create your template but as soon as you start a new spreadsheet, you have to do it all over again.  What a pain!!!  Also HELP takes you to a link that is no longer available.  Not to mention that this hasn't been updated since mid 2013.  I guess they are just no longer supporting it.  Too bad as I think it has potential!
This app has no substance. It doesnt have a built i  scanner. It just makes you download a different app to use as a scanner

I used a free scan to file,  then email it to myself, then edit it. Now I can skip multiple steps. PROS: Once you learn how to use it,  it works. CONS: Poor documentation! There are no Android tutorial, and iPhone version looks very different. Android tip - press & hold your phone's menu button (bottom left) to see the apps menu, including email function. For $0.99 is worth the hassle.  Can't wait until this gets updated to 4.0 (supposed to happen back in Dec 2013) with a friendlier Android interface.
Can you use a Bluetooth wireless barcode scanner?

Program works...  but when you  annotation find the file it creates (yes I even searched my storage with Astro)  what's the point?  There are also no menus to check program settings etc...  perhaps it's my device...  so if you have a Samsung Note 5 stay away.
replyContent:
You'll need to long press the menu button to export.

The menu is still there.  Long press the task switch button.
You'll find this works in other apps and Android tasks.

http://www.androidcentral.com/samsung-galaxy-s5-menu-button-hidden

content: I needed something to quickly scan a bunch of product box barcodes into a spreadsheet.  It's nice that it can continuously scan multiple barcodes and put each one into its own csv row.  I was able to email the CSV file to myself, and then any manipulation I needed (parsing out the scan to multiple columns) I could do in Excel.    It doesn't have a lot of bells and whistles, but I didn't expect them for what I paid for this.  This was on a Nexus 5 with lollipop, so it does work with the latest revision of Android.
Would be an awesome app to purchase of developer maintained it. Extremely useful if it does work.

content: It takes a lot longer to scan barcodes but other than that, works great.
Simple app, great for retail inventory reporting, will be better if it could insert data between rows.
scanner is just inferior. Takes longer to recognise barcodes than other scanners.

This did exactly what I needed it to do, scan barcodes into a spreadsheet. I used it to inventory 90 hard drives and it read them in just fine. There was a good audible notification that the scan was successful.  A feature that would be nice would be to reduce the scan window so that you can get exactly what you are looking for in the event there are a lot of barcodes close together.  Emailed a CSV perfectly.

The app does what is intended to do which is scanning barcodes and organizing the data for you. I suggest implementing the ability to scan with Bluetooth devices or transfer data to computers via Bluetooth. I think those two suggestions will increase the productivity of the app. Overall its not bad.

This is not flexible enough.  You can enter related data with your scanned barcode but you have to backspace over the old data to enter new data rather than it allowing you to enter a row then start with a clear row.  If your relevant data is redundant for many barcodes then it will work for you otherwise it is either a waste of money or just inefficient to use. 15 min is not enough time to sample the app so google play kinda sucks as well.
Does not link to my email
I guess it's hit or miss, but definitely a hit for me. The app is no frills but does exactly what I need and it works perfectly.

I tried  to use this for over 30 minutes it did not make scanning an inventory any easier.  Interface is simple, but its scanning to fields ability is very limited and causes many errors.  I actually just wound up typing it.  Save your time and money and avoid this.

My motorola barcode scanner took a dump and I needed something to get me by for about 3 hours. The app seems to be working fine I stopped after about 30 items. When I went back to try to review what I had done there was nothing there. You guys could have been a hero today but instead you're a 0 I wish I could give this minus 1.

I work at a local painting and contracting company whose workers regularly check out equipment for various jobs. We are working on barcoding all of the equipment with generated codes so that they can be scanned and emailed in a spreadsheet, using this app, to my inbox. From there I can see and assign the equipment to each worker using our main application. This allows me to avoid stacks of paperwork that were originally used when signing out equipment. I'm highly appreciative of this app. Thank you!
Would give it 5 star but file can't be opened when you email it. This makes it worthless for me. Going to keep it in hopes this is fixed. What program opens spread sheet?
